# Al Reem Hospital

## Project Overview

**Al Reem Hospital** is a modern multi-specialty healthcare facility on **Reem Island, Abu Dhabi**, established in **2020** and operated by **VAMED** in partnership with **Charité**. The hospital includes **200+ beds**, advanced inpatient and outpatient care, dedicated **post-acute rehabilitation**, and **30+ medical specialties**, with a strong focus on complex care and value-based clinical outcomes.

## My Role

On this project, my contribution focused on the intersection of **facility planning, BIM collaboration, and system integration**. My responsibility was not only to support the digital building model as a design and delivery tool, but also to help position it as a practical foundation for future hospital operations and facility management.

I worked across disciplines to align the building information model with the needs of facility teams, operational workflows, and long-term asset use. This included supporting coordination between design information, technical systems, and data structures required for a more connected and maintainable healthcare environment.

## Key Responsibilities

- Supported **BIM collaboration** across project stakeholders to improve coordination between architectural, technical, and operational requirements  
- Helped structure project information to support **facility management use**, not only design delivery  
- Contributed to the integration logic between the **BIM model**, building assets, and facility-related system data  
- Considered how spaces, equipment, and technical systems could be linked to future **operations, maintenance, and lifecycle management** processes  
- Bridged communication between design intent and operational functionality, with attention to usability for facility and maintenance teams  

## BIM and Facility Management Integration

A key value of the project was the opportunity to connect the hospital’s digital model with a future-facing **facility management solution**. In this approach, the BIM model acts as a central source of building information, connecting geometry, room data, asset information, and technical system references into one coordinated environment.

This type of integration can support:

- **Asset and equipment tracking** with linked specifications, maintenance history, and warranties  
- **Preventive maintenance planning** for MEP systems and critical hospital infrastructure  
- **Space and department management** with accurate room-level data  
- **Visual work order coordination** using model-based location intelligence  
- **Lifecycle and replacement planning** for key building systems and medical support infrastructure  
- **Better system integration** between the building model, operational databases, and FM platforms  

## Portfolio Relevance

This project reflects my broader professional focus: using **BIM as a bridge between design, operations, and digital facility management**. It demonstrates my interest in making building data more usable beyond handover — supporting collaboration, system integration, and smarter long-term management of complex healthcare facilities.

## Summary

Al Reem Hospital is a strong example of how healthcare design and digital delivery can support future operations. My role was centered on strengthening the relationship between **facility needs, BIM collaboration, and integrated system thinking**, helping create a more connected foundation for efficient building management over the full lifecycle.